This paper discusses a task parallel platform designed for modern NUMA architectures, which involves topics related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and parallel programming (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the implementation of the platform, which involves topics related to computer architecture (cs.AR) and performance analysis (cs.PF). Finally, the paper proposes a new scheduling algorithm, which involves topics related to control systems (cs.SY).
